Richmond & Danville Railroad.
Fourth of July Excursion to Amelia Springs.
Great Military Display.
Tournament and Ball.
An Extra train will leave Richmond st 4 o'clock A.M., on Wednesday, the 4th of July, and arrive at Jetersville in time for breakfast at the Amelia Springs. Passengers by this train can spend the day at the Springs and attend the Ball at night. Passengers going by the 7 o'clock regular train reach the Springs at 10:30, returning to Richmond by the train at 12 o'clock at night. Tickets for the round trip. $2.
je 30'-5t
R.E. Hughson, Ticket Agent